how can i encourage myself to test my blood for sugar more frequently i don't take any medicine for diabetes yet but i am the only family member who doesn't i'm trying to get my weight down and it's working with exercise and that helps i'm borderline right now and want to avoid meds or damage from diabetes i've been testing and the trend line is going down but sometimes i just don't feel like it for a couple of days and sometimes i only do it once a day how can i get myself into a regular routine of tests that will better help my doctor see where i am you are like us all diabetes testing can be a bore and we all get a bit depressed having to live with this medical problem but remember there is always some one else that is worse off than you or me so be glad that this is all you suffer from one way is to make your self a blood sugar graph and each day try and get the readings lower as you are with exercises etc with a colour graph you see the levels easily test your self when you get up and then b or after each meal the other incentive is as you have said want to avoid damage from diabetes try and think what it would be like to be blind or crippled due to nerve damage Diabetes mellitus Hypoglycemia Insulin Hyperglycemia Fecal incontinence Atherosclerosis Chronic fatigue syndrome Prostate cancer Dieting Coeliac disease Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Stomach cancer Folic acid Gastroparesis Diabetic retinopathy Urinary incontinence Diabetic neuropathy Insulin resistance Alzheimer's disease Medicine Stroke Polycystic ovary syndrome Obesity Hypertension Alcoholism Weight training Erectile dysfunction Chlorpromazine Atkins Nutritional Approach Binge eating disorder Traumatic brain injury Tocopherol Blood sugar Bipolar disorder Breastfeeding Asthma Clinical depression Crohn's disease Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Nutrition Aspartame Gout Low-carbohydrate diet Glaucoma Glucose meter Anorexia nervosa First aid Anxiety Angina Lupus erythematosus Non-Hodgkin's l